well, the Kardashians have one of those to release when the time is right…

00:14:28.872 --> 00:14:34.142
Then the sex tape got released, and Kim Kardashian went from nowhere

00:14:34.452 --> 00:14:38.732
to the talk of the town, or at least the talk of some American tabloid

00:14:38.732 --> 00:14:43.672
press, and this provided the perfect launchpad for the TV series.

00:14:45.212 --> 00:14:49.612
And this brings us neatly to the question of authenticity.

00:14:51.122 --> 00:14:56.152
Everything about the Kardashians revolved around the idea of authenticity.

00:14:56.972 --> 00:15:01.982
They came to fame with “reality” TV, a TV series that was

00:15:01.982 --> 00:15:07.172
supposedly unscripted and followed their real day-to-day lives.

00:15:07.992 --> 00:15:13.902
They sold and continue to sell products that they tell their fans they use themselves, their

00:15:13.902 --> 00:15:19.902
entire brand is based on building an authentic connection between them and their followers.

00:15:21.042 --> 00:15:24.262
But there are plenty of examples that indicate that

00:15:24.262 --> 00:15:27.662
their authenticity might not be quite what it seems.

00:15:29.092 --> 00:15:32.972
For starters, let’s talk about appearance, as everything

00:15:32.982 --> 00:15:35.422
with the Kardashians revolves around appearance.

00:15:37.052 --> 00:15:42.552
For years, Kylie Jenner denied having any kind of surgical work done on

00:15:42.552 --> 00:15:46.702
her lips, despite the fact that they were clearly much larger than before.

00:15:47.882 --> 00:15:53.682
Finally, she admitted, yes, she had had lip filler work done to enlarge her lips.

00:15:54.642 --> 00:15:58.002
Kim denied that she had had work done on her bottom

00:15:58.222 --> 00:16:01.032
to make it larger, and then admitted that she had.

00:16:02.582 --> 00:16:06.852
And their social media photos are always released with heavy

00:16:06.852 --> 00:16:11.122
filters, hiding any kind of blemishes or wrinkles or spots.

00:16:12.362 --> 00:16:18.612
Sure, there might not be anything inherently wrong with this, but if you are selling a product

00:16:18.952 --> 00:16:23.782
and telling your followers that buying this product will make you look like the person in the

00:16:23.782 --> 00:16:29.922
picture, and the person in the picture has been heavily edited, then it is somewhat deceptive.

00:16:31.102 --> 00:16:35.162
Now, whenever the Kardashians have been caught out for doing this, they have

00:16:35.162 --> 00:16:39.762
been quick to talk about the perils of social media and how having hundreds of

00:16:39.762 --> 00:16:44.072
millions of people following your every move means that every inch of your body

00:16:44.072 --> 00:16:49.162
is scrutinised, and this has unfortunately caused them to take certain actions.

00:16:50.702 --> 00:16:55.842
You might have some sympathy for this, but it’s also important to remember that this

00:16:55.872 --> 00:17:00.702
media attention and fame is something that has been carefully developed over almost

00:17:00.702 --> 00:17:06.102
20 years and has made the family billions of dollars; it is something that they have

00:17:06.142 --> 00:17:11.082
actively sought out and they use to sell their wares to people all around the world.

00:17:12.242 --> 00:17:14.502
And their influence is vast.

00:17:15.402 --> 00:17:17.552
Perhaps you see this where you live.

00:17:18.412 --> 00:17:19.182
I certainly do.

00:17:19.812 --> 00:17:25.462
The look of large “filled” lips, painted eyebrows and heavily contoured makeup is

00:17:25.462 --> 00:17:30.032
something that has almost single handedly been popularised by the Kardashian family.

00:17:31.372 --> 00:17:36.942
For better or for worse, they influence the decisions and styles of hundreds of

00:17:36.942 --> 00:17:43.072
millions of people all over the world, and no doubt future historians will look back at

00:17:43.072 --> 00:17:49.702
photos of people in 2023 and say “that look was popularised by the Kardashian family”.

00:17:51.062 --> 00:17:56.382
And like them or loathe them, one has to admit that the Kardashian family have mastered

00:17:56.442 --> 00:18:02.442
the art of celebrity and social media, walking a fine line between reality and performance.

00:18:03.122 --> 00:18:07.782
They've actively crafted personas that feed into a lucrative business model,

00:18:08.332 --> 00:18:13.552
one that promises reality yet often delivers a carefully edited version of it.

00:18:14.942 --> 00:18:18.062
But how long will this success continue?

00:18:18.892 --> 00:18:22.396
The Kardashians shot to worldwide fame during the

00:18:22.716 --> 00:18:26.312
"Instagram era", which many would argue has already peaked.

00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:31.082
This era was all about wanting to look perfect and put together,

00:18:31.542 --> 00:18:35.222
which explains why the Kardashians were so desirable at the time.

00:18:35.922 --> 00:18:41.812
Their heavily edited photos and strategic Instagram posts were illusions of perfection.

00:18:42.932 --> 00:18:47.652
But in 2023, to the millions of people who would have been their

00:18:47.652 --> 00:18:51.792
customers, authenticity is valued more highly than perfection.

00:18:52.702 --> 00:18:57.542
So, the question remains, how will the Kardashians adapt to this new world?

00:18:58.172 --> 00:19:00.912
Will they manage to remain relevant in the years to come?

00:19:01.612 --> 00:19:05.662
Or have they spent so much of their existence promoting a fake

00:19:05.662 --> 00:19:09.082
reality that they no longer know what authentic really means?

00:19:10.692 --> 00:19:15.942
Who knows, but if the past 15 years are anything to go by, it seems that

00:19:15.942 --> 00:19:20.712
there is no length the Kardashian family is not willing to go to be famous.

